DataElement.preferredDefinition: A class of publication in which original scientific work is described.  The format usually includes an introduction in which relevant concepts are identified and the experimental system under study is presented, a section describing the experiments that were performed to test a specific hypothesis and the results and observations that were obtained, a section in which the results are discussed relative to findings by other investigators and the current state of knowledge in the field, and a section describing the experimental methods and procedures in sufficient detail to enable the reproduction of the work by independent investigators.:Where something is available or from where it originates._The period of time that it takes for Earth to make a complete revolution around the sun; a period of time containing 365 days._Value Domain for java language Integer datatype
